
[December 1775]. Petition for reimbursement of damages sustained on the Quebec expedition. Some of your Pettitioners By Reason of the Badness of the Weather, at the Cold Season of the Year, Suffered Considerable Losses, by going up the River; and others by being Destitude of Provisions were obliged to Leave the Detachment and Return back from Sd Expedition; were at Considerable Expence in traviling, and
[627]
not heaving Any Allowance of Provision, were obliged to Bare our own Expences.1
